            <bug_when>2009-01-13 09:54:37 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>It would be good addition to implement to add an event called beforeChangeSelected. If you e.g. want to change the tab, you could also show a dialog before.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>7311</commentid>
            <who name="Fabian Jakobs">fabian.jakobs</who>
            <bug_when>2009-01-13 14:08:34 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The tabview uses a radio manger to handle the selection. It would make sense to add an &quot;beforeChangeSelected&quot; event to the radio manager and forward it to the tabview. To do this the selected property of the radio manager has to be rewritten as getter setter pair. Before setting the value the &quot;beforeChangeSelected&quot; event has to be fired and only if this event was not prevented the new value has to be set.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
